SIMPLE: rowel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rowel
<hw>Row"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>roele</ets>,
<ets>rouele</ets>, properly, a little wheel, F. <ets>rouelle</ets>
collop, slice, LL. <ets>rotella</ets> a little wheel, dim. of L.
<ets>rota</ets> a wheel. See <er>Roll</er>, and cf.
<er>Rota</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The little wheel of a spur, with
sharp points.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With sounding whip, and <qex>rowels</qex> dyed in blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A little flat ring or wheel on horses'
bits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The iron <qex>rowels</qex> into frothy foam he bit.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A roll of hair, silk, etc., passed
through the flesh of horses, answering to a seton in human
surgery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rowel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rowel
<hw>Row"el</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Roweled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Rowelled</conjf>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Roweling</conjf> or
<conjf>Rowelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>To insert a
rowel, or roll of hair or silk, into (as the flesh of a horse).</def>
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rowel bone</ent>⟦br⟧
